            <h2 class="text-center">Gym Ethics</h2>
            <hr>
            <p>
                Gym ethics are principles and guidelines that govern proper behavior and conduct in a gym environment. Adhering to gym ethics ensures a positive experience for all gym-goers and fosters a respectful and supportive community.
            </p>
            <h3>Key Gym Ethics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Respect others' space: Be mindful of personal space and equipment usage. Avoid monopolizing equipment or leaving weights scattered around.</li>
                <li>Clean up after yourself: Wipe down equipment after use and return any weights or accessories to their proper place.</li>
                <li>Follow gym rules: Familiarize yourself with the gym's rules and policies, including proper attire, noise levels, and time limits on equipment.</li>
                <li>Be considerate: Be mindful of others' workout routines and avoid disrupting them. Wait your turn for equipment and offer to share if necessary.</li>
                <li>Support fellow gym-goers: Encourage and motivate others, offer assistance if needed, and refrain from making negative comments or judgments.</li>
                <li>Practice proper hygiene: Shower before entering the gym, wear clean workout attire, and use deodorant to minimize body odor.</li>
                <li>Respect gym staff: Treat gym staff with courtesy and respect, and follow their instructions or guidance when necessary.</li>
                <li>Report any issues: Notify gym staff of any safety hazards, equipment malfunctions, or concerns regarding other gym-goers' behavior.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                By adhering to these gym ethics, you contribute to creating a positive and welcoming gym environment for everyone.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


